amdgpu: uvd_v4_2 — write Sony IOCTL constants at region 2/3[0] (v76d-β-2-A15)

A8 wrote plain region sizes (0x124000, 0x4000) at region 2[0]/3[0].
Result: neutral (no effect on STATUS bit 1).

A15: try Sony's IOCTL-returned constants instead. From the Ghidra
dungeon-map:

  IOCTL 0x4008830c returns 0x300308000
    = 0x300000000 + total region size
    Sony's userspace receives this — likely the "first user-allocatable
    VA" hint after the 3 reserved regions.

  IOCTL 0x4004830b returns 0x20000
    = 128 KB, possibly a buffer/ring size constant.

If the fw expects the host to set up these specific values at region
2/3[0] before VCPU release, A15 unblocks STATUS bit 1. They're
better-grounded guesses than A8's plain sizes since they're values
Sony's actual userspace code observes.

Layout written by A15:
  region2[0]   = 0x300308000  (u64)
  region2[1]   = 0x20000      (u64)
  region3[0]   = 0x300308000  (u64)
  region3[1]   = 0x20000      (u64)

Expected:
  ✅ STATUS bit 1 sets — Sony's IOCTL constants were the missing
     "host setup". Narrow down in follow-up which of the four writes
     mattered.
  🟡 Cache sample table changes in a meaningful way (different sync
     pattern) → fw read something different. Continue with variations.
  ❌ Identical sample table → these constants aren't the gate. Pivot
     to A16 (SBL Ghidra) or B1 (per-vmid PD).

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

